  "analytical_observations": [
    "BU STRUCTURE: The BU beta sheet is the exclusive vehicle for BU-level cash analysis. It runs the same row structure across all 6 files (Sears Stores, Kmart, Home Services, KCD, Supply Chain, CITI, Cross Country, etc.) with monthly time-series columns.",
    "CASH FLOW SHEET: Entirely consolidated \u2014 no BU breakdown. ~40 columns track daily operating cash flows, available/unavailable cash buckets, debt tranches, and liquidity surplus/deficit metrics.",
    "KCD TRANSFORMATION: KCD inflows collapsed FY22-FY25 (loss of Sears internal transactions) then projected to surge to $42M FY26 and $77M FY27 \u2014 likely reflecting a new external brand licensing/royalty strategy.",
    "HOME SERVICES DOMINANCE: HS was 47-49% of total operating inflows in FY22 and remains ~60% of the much smaller FY26 base \u2014 still the core business.",
    "PAYROLL REDUCTION: Direct payroll fell from -$391M FY22 to -$196M FY26 (50% reduction) \u2014 tracking the revenue decline roughly proportionally.",
    "ASSURANT EXIT: Home Services Assurant payments fell from -$101M FY22 to -$0.5M FY27 \u2014 the Assurant warranty partnership is essentially wound down.",
